Description:
Don’t show up looking like you got dressed in the dark! 🌚@atucareercloset is here to help! 🙌🏼

Account name: ATU LeMoyne Smith School of Business
Description:
This Women’s History Month, the College of Business and Economic Development is highlighting amazing women in Business, Agriculture, and Tourism in our community ✨

Today, we are honoring the remarkable impact of Danielle and Sidney from Main Street Russellville! These dynamic women are at the heart of some of the most anticipated events in our community, including the acclaimed Moon Over Main eclipse festival, Art Walk, and Fall Festival. Their tireless work behind the scenes not only enhances the local culture, but also plays a key role in driving tourism to Russellville!

Recently recognized with the Natural State Tourism Development Award at the 2025 Henry Awards, Danielle and Sidney are essential to the economic growth of our town through their event planning, collaboration, and unwavering commitment to creating memorable experiences for all. Their contributions to both the tourism sector and the community at large are truly invaluable!

We’re especially proud to highlight Sidney as a management student in our department, where she continues to apply the skills and knowledge she gains in the classroom to her work in the community. Her ability to balance her academic pursuits with her role in shaping local tourism is a true testament to her dedication and leadership!

{ #ATUBusiness #ArkansasTech #WomensHistoryMonth #ATU2025 #RussellvilleAR #ArkansasLife #ArkansasMade #WomensMonth #WomenInBusiness }
